1
00:00:00,953 --> 00:00:04,256
[Lawn mower whirring]

2
00:00:27,706 --> 00:00:29,273
Found a phone!

3
00:00:30,460 --> 00:00:33,172
It looks like it's from
1967, but I think it'll work.

4
00:00:33,197 --> 00:00:34,859
Just a sec, Jimmy.

5
00:00:35,437 --> 00:00:37,732
Excellent. Thank you
for being so careful.

6
00:00:37,768 --> 00:00:39,134
- Sir.
- Hmm?

7
00:00:39,169 --> 00:00:41,102
- We have to get in your attic.
- For what?

8
00:00:41,138 --> 00:00:42,422
Oh, the hook-up.

9
00:00:42,447 --> 00:00:43,613
Oh, no. That's all right. Don't bother.

10
00:00:43,638 --> 00:00:44,984
Oh, it won't take 20 minutes.

11
00:00:45,009 --> 00:00:46,577
Plus, you really can't
use it if I don't do it.

12
00:00:46,602 --> 00:00:48,368
No, it's all right. We're not gonna...

13
00:00:48,404 --> 00:00:49,770
Uh, when you're done here,

14
00:00:49,805 --> 00:00:51,471
would you get some more
lamps in the garage?

15
00:00:51,507 --> 00:00:52,739
- Thanks.
- [Pounding]

16
00:00:52,775 --> 00:00:54,141
[Man speaks Spanish]

17
00:00:54,176 --> 00:00:55,609
- So, we got a phone.
- Yeah.

18
00:00:55,644 --> 00:00:56,834
The yard's half-mowed.

19
00:00:56,859 --> 00:00:58,979
Uh, the sockets and
stuff are looking a-ok.

20
00:00:59,014 --> 00:01:01,081
I'm gonna check again just to make sure.

21
00:01:01,116 --> 00:01:02,382
We're almost there.

22
00:01:02,418 --> 00:01:03,450
[Chuckling] Good. Good.

23
00:01:03,485 --> 00:01:05,919
Um, what do you think?

24
00:01:05,955 --> 00:01:08,288
On? Off?

25
00:01:08,324 --> 00:01:11,325
Ohh. I think... off.

26
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:14,127
Yeah. You're right. Off it is.

27
00:01:14,163 --> 00:01:15,692
- Chuck.
- Hmm?

28
00:01:15,717 --> 00:01:17,465
You sure this is the right play?

29
00:01:17,490 --> 00:01:18,799
I mean, in my experience,

30
00:01:18,834 --> 00:01:22,459
the bigger the lie, the
harder it can be to dig out.

31
00:01:22,890 --> 00:01:25,459
I'll cross that bridge
when I come to it.

32
00:01:28,168 --> 00:01:29,216
[Sighs]

33
00:01:29,241 --> 00:01:31,078
Hey, guys, think we're
set with the lamps.

34
00:01:31,113 --> 00:01:34,414
Uh, could someone give me a
hand with this phone? Gracias.

35
00:01:34,450 --> 00:01:37,284
[Match strikes]

36
00:02:11,687 --> 00:02:13,655
[Sizzling]

37
00:02:29,686 --> 00:02:30,978
Mmm.

38
00:02:35,236 --> 00:02:38,376
[Indistinct conversation in distance]

39
00:02:47,990 --> 00:02:49,189
[Knock on door]

40
00:02:49,224 --> 00:02:50,724
It's open!

41
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:52,159
[Door opens]

42
00:02:54,471 --> 00:02:55,703
[Door closes]

43
00:02:59,742 --> 00:03:01,075
Rebecca.

44
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:03,136
- Chuck.
- You look lovely.

45
00:03:03,172 --> 00:03:05,338
- Oh, it's so good to see you.
- [Chuckles] And you.

46
00:03:05,384 --> 00:03:06,397
[Chuckles]

47
00:03:06,422 --> 00:03:07,522
- Oh.
- [Chuckling] Hey,

48
00:03:07,547 --> 00:03:09,256
what's with the candles?

49
00:03:09,281 --> 00:03:10,600
Why you sittin' here in the dark?

50
00:03:10,625 --> 00:03:12,179
Ye, I was wondering the same thing.

51
00:03:12,214 --> 00:03:15,489
Oh, my God, the afternoon I've had.

52
00:03:15,514 --> 00:03:17,684
Two hours ago, I take the sea bass out.

53
00:03:17,709 --> 00:03:20,387
No sooner is it prepped and resting

54
00:03:20,412 --> 00:03:22,823
then, boom... power goes down.

55
00:03:22,858 --> 00:03:25,121
I get on the phone to the city.

56
00:03:25,146 --> 00:03:26,545
To make a long story short,

57
00:03:26,570 --> 00:03:29,763
those bozos at PNM mixed up my payment.

58
00:03:29,798 --> 00:03:32,666
The deadbeat at 512 San Cristobal

59
00:03:32,701 --> 00:03:34,434
hasn't been paying his bills.

60
00:03:34,470 --> 00:03:36,036
And, of course, I'm...

61
00:03:36,071 --> 00:03:38,864
- 215. Mm-hmm. Mm.
- 215, exactly.

62
00:03:38,889 --> 00:03:41,007
They say they'll have
it on again by tomorrow.

63
00:03:41,043 --> 00:03:44,444
In the meantime, I borrowed some
camping gear from my neighbors.

64
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:46,883
Hence, the rustic flair.

65
00:03:46,908 --> 00:03:48,115
- Jeez.
- Oh, yeah.

66
00:03:48,150 --> 00:03:49,549
So, what do we do?

67
00:03:49,585 --> 00:03:51,765
Uh, get out of here
and go to a restaurant?

68
00:03:51,790 --> 00:03:54,380
We could hit Seasons. Your treat.

69
00:03:54,405 --> 00:03:56,703
We could, yeah.

70
00:03:56,728 --> 00:03:59,092
But, um, you know,
dinner's almost ready.

71
00:03:59,128 --> 00:04:01,361
And the fish... I would have
just had to throw it out.

72
00:04:01,396 --> 00:04:03,029
All I have to do is toss it in a pan.

73
00:04:03,065 --> 00:04:04,765
How about we just rough it?

74
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,099
Huh? You okay with that?

75
00:04:06,135 --> 00:04:07,901
Uh, um...

76
00:04:07,936 --> 00:04:10,971
Well... why not? It'll be fun.

77
00:04:11,006 --> 00:04:13,774
We'll do an haute-cuisine camp-out.

78
00:04:13,809 --> 00:04:16,568
Great! Then it's settled.
Let me take that. Take your...

79
00:04:16,593 --> 00:04:17,839
- Oh, yeah, here. Oh, thank you.
- Here, I'll take that.

80
00:04:17,864 --> 00:04:19,497
Mm-hmm.

81
00:04:22,202 --> 00:04:23,825
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

82
00:04:23,850 --> 00:04:25,435
Oh, my God.

83
00:04:25,460 --> 00:04:27,827
- I can't eat another bite.
- [Chuckles]

84
00:04:29,758 --> 00:04:32,392
Cheers to the Galloping Gourmet.

85
00:04:32,417 --> 00:04:33,834
- Mm!
- Ah.

86
00:04:33,859 --> 00:04:34,958
- Yeah.
- [Glasses clink]

87
00:04:34,993 --> 00:04:36,493
- [Laughs]
- Mm.

88
00:04:37,551 --> 00:04:39,084
The Calvados is perfect.

89
00:04:39,109 --> 00:04:41,164
Mm. You always liked it.

90
00:04:41,507 --> 00:04:42,835
[Clears throat] Here.

91
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:44,249
Uh, um...

92
00:04:44,274 --> 00:04:45,343
- Let me get this.
- No, no, Jimmy.

93
00:04:45,368 --> 00:04:46,693
- You don't have to.
- No, least I can do...

94
00:04:46,718 --> 00:04:48,403
- ... is the dishes.
- Oh.

95
00:04:48,428 --> 00:04:49,998
Thank you.

96
00:04:50,023 --> 00:04:51,860
- [Chuckles]
- Thanks, Jimmy.

97
00:04:55,343 --> 00:04:57,804
This turned out better
than I thought. [Chuckles]

98
00:04:58,382 --> 00:05:00,927
Uh, I'm so... sorry about the lights.

99
00:05:00,952 --> 00:05:03,725
Oh, it's nice. Atmospheric.

100
00:05:04,322 --> 00:05:08,258
I mean, I still can't get
over Jimmy being a lawyer.

101
00:05:08,293 --> 00:05:09,979
Neither can I.

102
00:05:10,004 --> 00:05:12,106
He's got his own shingle
out and everything.

103
00:05:12,131 --> 00:05:13,817
I mean, a real, responsible citizen.

104
00:05:13,842 --> 00:05:15,632
I mean, who woulda thought?

105
00:05:15,667 --> 00:05:16,924
Yeah.

106
00:05:16,949 --> 00:05:18,244
[Chuckles]

107
00:05:18,870 --> 00:05:20,369
Mm.

108
00:05:21,424 --> 00:05:23,339
This place is the same.

109
00:05:23,375 --> 00:05:25,441
I mean, I-I would've thought you'd...

110
00:05:25,477 --> 00:05:27,346
[Breathes deeply]

111
00:05:27,371 --> 00:05:29,010
change things up.

112
00:05:29,035 --> 00:05:30,501
Move things around.

113
00:05:30,526 --> 00:05:33,227
You've got great taste.
And if it ain't broke...

114
00:05:34,354 --> 00:05:35,818
How's the tour going?

115
00:05:35,854 --> 00:05:36,971
It's good. Good.

116
00:05:36,996 --> 00:05:38,796
- Um, the Far East this fall.
- Oh.

117
00:05:38,821 --> 00:05:41,134
Uh, China, South Korea, and Vietnam.

118
00:05:41,159 --> 00:05:43,006
- That's gonna be exciting.
- Yeah.

119
00:05:43,031 --> 00:05:45,482
And then, um, after Santa Fe this week,

120
00:05:45,507 --> 00:05:48,349
- uh, we're back to Central Europe.
- And it's good?

121
00:05:48,435 --> 00:05:50,168
- Well, it's a lot of hotels.
- Yeah.

122
00:05:50,214 --> 00:05:52,414
I mean, in Budapest,
I think I saw mostly

123
00:05:52,449 --> 00:05:55,497
the inside of the concert
hall and the Marriott.

124
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:58,186
But, you know, I shouldn't complain.

125
00:05:58,222 --> 00:06:01,216
You're not complaining.
You're observing.

126
00:06:04,561 --> 00:06:06,461
Did you finally get to see Salzburg?

127
00:06:06,497 --> 00:06:09,170
[Breathes deeply] Not yet,
but next month, after Vienna.

128
00:06:09,248 --> 00:06:11,767
Do you remember when we
tried to go to Salzburg?

129
00:06:11,802 --> 00:06:14,202
And that crazy old
lady on the scooter...

130
00:06:14,229 --> 00:06:16,997
- Oh, yes! Yes! [Laughs]
- ... chased us out of the train station.

131
00:06:17,022 --> 00:06:18,686
Yeah! And then, um...

132
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:20,223
and then we went and got, uh,

133
00:06:20,248 --> 00:06:23,809
it was a-a-a raspberry
Linzer torte in Innsbruck?

134
00:06:23,834 --> 00:06:25,575
- Mm.
- To make ourselves feel better?

135
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:27,783
Mm. [Chuckles] You said,
"We'll never finish this!"

136
00:06:27,818 --> 00:06:28,991
And then we did.

137
00:06:29,016 --> 00:06:30,609
[Both laughing]

138
00:06:32,327 --> 00:06:34,823
So, what's after Asia? Any
plans for a stateside tour?

139
00:06:34,873 --> 00:06:37,272
[Sighs] Oh, you know,
hopefully next year.

140
00:06:37,311 --> 00:06:40,128
You know, maybe a residency.
Oh, that would be sweet.

141
00:06:40,164 --> 00:06:41,563
I mean, you know, I like the buses

142
00:06:41,598 --> 00:06:43,655
and trains and planes fine,

143
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:45,202
but I, um...

144
00:06:45,756 --> 00:06:49,350
I miss having one...
one place to hang my hat.

145
00:06:51,642 --> 00:06:53,608
[Cellphone ringing]

146
00:06:53,644 --> 00:06:54,977
[Suspenseful music plays]

147
00:06:55,012 --> 00:06:57,179
Oh, God!

148
00:06:57,214 --> 00:06:59,815
I'm sorry. I-I-I hate that thing.

149
00:06:59,850 --> 00:07:02,985
I feel like I'm on a leash. Ugh!

150
00:07:03,616 --> 00:07:05,003
I'm sorry.

151
00:07:05,028 --> 00:07:07,195
[Ringing continues]

152
00:07:08,709 --> 00:07:10,809
Oh. Oh, it's my conductor.

153
00:07:10,834 --> 00:07:13,661
Um, I have to take this. I'm sorry.

154
00:07:13,686 --> 00:07:15,163
H-Hi, Andre.

155
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:17,655
No, I'm just at dinner. What's up?

156
00:07:18,397 --> 00:07:19,801
Well, I can do that at rehearsal.

157
00:07:19,837 --> 00:07:21,997
Yeah, no problem. Yeah.

158
00:07:22,022 --> 00:07:25,307
No, I-I know that they're
coming in late on bar 16.

159
00:07:25,342 --> 00:07:27,843
Y-Yeah. Got it. Got it.

160
00:07:27,878 --> 00:07:29,678
I will make sure that...

161
00:07:29,713 --> 00:07:31,513
Uh, c-c-can you hold on a second?

162
00:07:31,548 --> 00:07:33,245
Let me just get a pen.

163
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:34,699
Mm-hmm.

164
00:07:35,660 --> 00:07:37,629
Yeah. No, I-I...

165
00:07:38,422 --> 00:07:40,455
Yeah, hold on one second.

166
00:07:40,491 --> 00:07:42,557
Yeah, I can do it... I
mean, whatever you need.

167
00:07:42,593 --> 00:07:44,159
Mm-hmm. Okay.

168
00:07:44,194 --> 00:07:45,394
All right, shoot.

169
00:07:45,429 --> 00:07:46,661
[Thumps table]

170
00:07:46,697 --> 00:07:48,630
Okay... [Speaking indistinctly]

171
00:07:49,418 --> 00:07:50,707
[Gasping]

172
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:51,798
Chuck?

173
00:07:52,348 --> 00:07:53,402
I'm all right.

174
00:07:53,437 --> 00:07:56,471
Well, do you want me to
rehearse the cellists separately?

175
00:07:56,507 --> 00:07:57,973
Jimmy: Rebecca. [Distorted] Rebecca.

176
00:07:58,008 --> 00:07:59,674
[Electricity buzzing]

177
00:08:01,011 --> 00:08:03,912
Well, no, it's not just
him. It's the whole section.

178
00:08:03,947 --> 00:08:05,590
Rebecca!

179
00:08:05,621 --> 00:08:06,848
Uh, no.

180
00:08:06,884 --> 00:08:08,871
[Distorted] T-That's fine.

181
00:08:08,896 --> 00:08:10,519
Yeah.

182
00:08:10,554 --> 00:08:12,715
[Cellphone clatters]
Chuck, what the hell?!

183
00:08:15,751 --> 00:08:17,225
Andre? [Sighs]

184
00:08:17,261 --> 00:08:19,561
I-I-I have to... I'll
have to call you back.

185
00:08:19,596 --> 00:08:21,072
- I'm sorry.
- [Cellphone beeps]

186
00:08:22,766 --> 00:08:25,136
What is your problem?

187
00:08:25,161 --> 00:08:27,561
[Breathing heavily]

188
00:08:27,586 --> 00:08:29,420
Say something.

189
00:08:33,572 --> 00:08:35,777
It is incredibly bad manners

190
00:08:35,813 --> 00:08:38,713
to answer a cellphone in company.

191
00:08:38,749 --> 00:08:40,734
It's very rude.

192
00:08:40,759 --> 00:08:43,930
Uh, I-I'm sorry.

193
00:08:43,955 --> 00:08:46,946
I-I didn't know that you felt that way.

194
00:08:46,971 --> 00:08:50,172
I... didn't mean to offend you, Chuck.

195
00:08:50,207 --> 00:08:52,341
[Chuckles] I-I may have overreacted.

196
00:08:52,376 --> 00:08:54,423
- That was very abrupt. Uh..
- No.

197
00:08:54,448 --> 00:08:56,283
I understand.

198
00:08:58,486 --> 00:08:59,837
- Uh...
- [Sighs]

199
00:09:00,626 --> 00:09:02,384
It's getting late.

200
00:09:02,419 --> 00:09:03,919
Thank you for a lovely dinner,

201
00:09:03,954 --> 00:09:06,322
but I should be getting
back to the hotel.

202
00:09:06,347 --> 00:09:08,256
Just gimme a minute, and we can...

203
00:09:08,292 --> 00:09:10,425
No. Uh, um, I'll just get a cab.

204
00:09:10,461 --> 00:09:11,627
I don't want to put you out
any more than I already...

205
00:09:11,652 --> 00:09:13,629
- Please, let me.
- No, really.

206
00:09:13,664 --> 00:09:15,664
A cab is the easiest.

207
00:09:17,564 --> 00:09:19,247
You gotta do somethin'.

208
00:09:19,279 --> 00:09:21,038
Y-You can't let her leave like this.

209
00:09:21,063 --> 00:09:23,538
- Just tell her what's going on.
- No. No.

210
00:09:23,574 --> 00:09:25,140
- [Rebecca speaking indistinctly]
- She'll understand.

211
00:09:25,175 --> 00:09:27,776
She'll... Would you rather
she think you're a raging prick

212
00:09:27,811 --> 00:09:29,192
than know the truth?

213
00:09:29,217 --> 00:09:30,428
No.

214
00:09:31,004 --> 00:09:32,814
Look, if you won't
tell her, then I will.

215
00:09:32,850 --> 00:09:34,716
No, no. No!

216
00:09:34,752 --> 00:09:36,397
You will not tell her.

217
00:09:36,987 --> 00:09:40,139
You... will not tell her.

218
00:09:40,897 --> 00:09:42,491
All right.

219
00:09:43,154 --> 00:09:45,614
Hi, Andre. Yes, I'm sorry about that.

220
00:09:45,639 --> 00:09:47,472
I dropped the phone.

