a boy fish from a girl fish.

229
00:10:32,785 --> 00:10:33,928
[Chuckling] Oh, yeah, see.

230
00:10:33,953 --> 00:10:35,889
Now I can see the lipstick.

231
00:10:36,084 --> 00:10:39,431
This is a living creature.
It's not a piece of furniture.

232
00:10:39,456 --> 00:10:41,423
So, after this, you take her home.

233
00:10:41,448 --> 00:10:43,955
You put her in a big
bowl, at least a gallon.

234
00:10:43,980 --> 00:10:45,908
- [Sighs]
- Get a good bubbler,

235
00:10:45,933 --> 00:10:47,478
maybe a plecostomus.

236
00:10:47,503 --> 00:10:49,173
And don't feed her too much.

237
00:10:49,198 --> 00:10:50,335
People get fat.

238
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:52,561
Fish, they drown in leftover food.

239
00:10:52,586 --> 00:10:54,553
All right already, Jacques Cousteau.

240
00:10:54,588 --> 00:10:55,921
Point made.

241
00:10:55,956 --> 00:10:57,289
Good.

242
00:11:00,132 --> 00:11:02,895
I'm guessing our friend
didn't refer you to me

243
00:11:02,930 --> 00:11:05,492
to get ichthyological advice.

244
00:11:06,023 --> 00:11:08,901
I'm looking for someone
with a light touch.

245
00:11:08,936 --> 00:11:12,076
I'm not talking some teenager
taking a five-finger discount

246
00:11:12,101 --> 00:11:13,605
on string cheese at the Stop 'N' Shop.

247
00:11:13,630 --> 00:11:15,975
I need highly skilled,

248
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,566
high-end, discreet.

249
00:11:18,612 --> 00:11:20,162
A real pro.

250
00:11:20,928 --> 00:11:23,498
You gotta fit him in a tight space?

251
00:11:23,757 --> 00:11:25,524
I don't think so.

252
00:11:27,621 --> 00:11:29,724
I got just the guy, then.

